The purely positive folks tried to gang up on me my previous post because they mad we do it better 🤣 purely negative huh… “LIMA” allegedly stands for least invasive minimally intrusive doesn’t that sound nice?! It’s a bastardization of Operant Conditioning to say you know what we should use punishment in this particular instance and make this type of correction because it helps the dog learn but nahh it doesnt align with our politics because we gotta use something “less invasive” Many of these people dont even believe in saying “no” to a dog these petsmart trainers i wonder how they’ll raise their children thinking time out is too harsh  KISS don’t over correct but don’t under correct either and use whatever helps THE DOG learn best and discard what doesnt. You can make reactivity progress fast if youre a trainer worth their salt, lowsy trainers take a long time to accomplish little and blame it on the dog. One of the main reasons reactivity takes longer to address is because the dog is going to have to encounter many different types of dogs large, small, intact or neutered, male, female etc.. other reactive dogs and non reactive dogs. But you can start leading your dogs immediately: adequately correct unwanted behaviors and reward good ones.  I’ve trained reactive dogs and fixed the issue in like a week. Harder cases will take a big longer and some dogs I believe have some sort of mental and or hormonal challenges but most of yalls dogs at home are relatively simple fixes humans created. It’s all love at the end of the day we all want what’s best for dogs but have vastly different ways of approaching things. Distracting a dog holding treats by your face or giving them a sniff command when a dog approaches is FAKE LAZY TRAINING IMO. That’s tip toeing around the issue.  #reactivedogs #crazypitbull #reactivedogtrainer #dogreactivity #purelypositivedoesnotexist #aversion #realdogtraining #balanceddogtrainer
